{{Infobox language |name = Angkola |nativename = |states = Indonesia |region = Sumatra (northern) |ethnicity = Angkola |speakers = 750,000 |date = 1991 |ref = e18 |familycolor= Austronesian |fam2 = [[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3 = [[Northwest Sumatran languages|Northwest Sumatran]] |fam4 = [[Batak languages|Batak]] |fam5 = Southern |fam7 = Angkola–Mandailing |iso3 = akb |glotto=bata1290 |glottorefname=Batak Angkola |script = [[Batak script|Batak]], [[Latin script|Latin]] }} {{Incubator|code=akb}} '''Angkola''', or '''Batak Angkola''', is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] of [[Sumatra]]. It is spoken in [[South Tapanuli Regency]] and [[Padang Sidempuan]].
