{{Distinguish|Lele language (Papua New Guinea)|Lele language (Chad)|Lele language (Guinea)}} {{Infobox language |name=Lele |nativename= |states=[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |region= |speakers=26,000 |date=1971 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C]]) |fam6=[[Bushoong languages|Bushoong]] (C.80) |iso3=lel |glotto=lele1265 |glottorefname=Lele (Democratic Republic of Congo) |guthrie=C.84 }}
'''Lele ''' (also spelled Bashilele, Usilele) is a language spoken mainly in the west edge of the [[Kasai-Occidental|Kasai-Occidental Province]], in [[Ilebo Territory|Ilebo]] and [[Tshikapa Territory|Tshikapa]] territories; the extreme east of the [[Bandundu Province]], in [[Idiofa Territory|Idiofa]] and [[Gungu Territory|Gungu]] territories of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
