{{Infobox language |name=Muteun |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |region= |ethnicity= |speakers=? |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=Hanoid |fam7=[[Akha language|Akha]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }}
'''Muteun''' (''{{IPA|mɔ˨˩tɯ˨˩}}'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]].
Muteun is spoken in [[Namo District]], [[Oudomxay Province|Oudomxai province]], including in Hunapha village (Kato 2008).
